<biogHist>
<abstract>The Children, Young Persons and Their Families Amendment Act 2009 (Act No.22/2009) amended the Children, Young Persons and Their Families Act 1997, following on from the release in 2006 of the 'Report on Child Protection Services in Tasmania'.</abstract>
<p>The key amendments made to the Children, Young Persons and Their Families Act in the 2009 legislation were:</p>
<list><item>the ability for mandatory reporters to report concerns about the care of children within their family to non-government Gateway Services</item>
<item>broader powers allowing the sharing of information relevant to the best interests of a child</item>
<item>the Secretary of the Department of Health and Human Services able to receive information relating to unborn children</item>
<item>greater options for permanent care arrangements in some cases</item>
<item>the creation of an Ashley Youth Detention Centre Residents' Advocate.</item></list>

</biogHist>
